@read ./base.ts

# module base

Shared ESLint flat config array that all environment-specific presets extend. Exports a `defineConfig` array as default — consumers spread it inside their own config.

Composes four rule layers in order:
1. `js.configs.recommended` — core JavaScript best practices
2. `tseslint.configs.recommended` — TypeScript-aware rules with type information (parser set to `tsconfig.json` at `process.cwd()`)
3. `importX.flatConfigs.recommended` + `importX.flatConfigs.typescript` — import ordering and resolution, with the TypeScript resolver pointing to the consuming package's `tsconfig.json`
4. `prettierPlugin` — Prettier formatting enforced as an ESLint error; all style rules that conflict with Prettier are disabled

Ignores: `.*.js`, `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `build/`, `eslint.config.ts`, `vite.config.ts`, `**/*_test.*`

Rule overrides applied on top of recommended sets:
- `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` → `off`
- `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` → `off`
- `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` → `warn` — enforces `import type` with `inline-type-imports` fix style
